result.value: Python package for performing lipidomics analyses
_Dylan H. Ross and Jang Ho Cho_

`lipydomics` is a Python package for performing standard lipidomics analysis protocols on data in an efficient and 
reproducible fashion. The primary modules in the package are `data`, `stats`, `plotting`, `identification` and 
`interactive`. The `data` module is responsible for storing lipidomics datasets, along with their associated metadata
and computed statistics. The `stats` module contains functions for computing statistics on a lipydomics `Dataset` 
instance and the `plotting` module has functions for generating various plots using computed statistics or the data
itself. The `identification` module has functions for identifying lipid features using different levels of information. 
The `interactive` module provides a more user-friendly text-based interface for performing lipidomics data analysis
for those who are not as familiar/comfortable with the more flexible Python API.

Documentation for the `lipydomics` API, organized by module, is available separately in [api.md](api.md). An example of 
a complete scripted analysis is included in [example_standard_analysis.py](example_standard_analysis.py). An additional 
example analysis (executed in a Jupyter notebook) is available [here](notebook_examples/API_Example.ipynb).

Documentation for the `lipydomics.interactive` module is available separately in [interactive.md](interactive.md). A
complete example demonstrating use of the interactive module (executed in a Jupyter notebook) is also available 
[here](notebook_examples/Interactive_Example.ipynb).

Documentation for the `lipydomics.interactive` module is available separately in [interactive.md](interactive.md). A
complete example demonstrating use of the interactive module (executed in a Jupyter notebook) is also available 
[here](notebook_examples/Interactive_Example.ipynb).

result.description:
This release brings an assortment of improvements and additions, highlights:
* General Bugfixes throughout
* Added some lipids to `LipidMass` (LCL, AcylPE, AlanylPG) and reclassified MGDG, DGDG, and GlcADG as glycolipids
* Added PLS-RA analysis with associated plotting and interactive functions
* Added Log2(fold-change) analysis with associated plotting function for generating heatmaps of lipid class changes between two groups
* Added two new TIMS-TOF lipid CCS datasets to lipid database
* Expanded and rebuilt theoretical database, improved CCS and RT prediction
* Reworked theoretical database build process
* Exposed CCS/RT prediction functions at the API level
result.name: More Improvements and Additions

result.description:
This release introduces a handful of updates and fixes to the initial feature-complete release, including:

* General Bug fixes
* Documentation split into multiple files and expanded
* Added another lipid CCS dataset to lipids.db and retrained predictive models
* Added a new identification level: theo_mz_rt
* Added descriptive headers to exported spreadsheet
* Added some utilities for batch data selection and plotting
* Made some changes for easier package installation
result.name: Updates to Initial Release

result.description:
This release is the first feature-complete version of lipydomics. All of the functionality has undergone basic testing and everything seems to work as intended.

Semantic versioning scheme:
Major version: 1 (API changes)
Minor version: 0 (back-compatible large feature additions)
Micro version: 0 (back-compatible bug fixes and small feature additions)
result.name: initial feature complete release
